comment11.params=
comment11.target=void\ move()
comment11.text=\n\ The\ robot\ will\ move\ to\ the\ next\ intersection\ in\ the\ direction\ it\ is\n\ facing,\ provided\ that\ its\ front\ is\ not\ blocked.\ If\ it\ is\ blocked\ it\ will\n\ generate\ an\ error\ and\ turn\ off.\ If\ it\ is\ not\ running\ it\ does\ nothing.\n
comment12.params=ignored
comment12.target=void\ move(int)
comment12.text=\ The\ argument\ is\ ignored\ for\ all\ robots.\ This\ is\ just\ move().\n\ \n
comment13.params=
comment13.target=void\ pickBeeper()
comment13.text=\n\ The\ robot\ will\ pick\ exactly\ one\ beeper\ from\ the\ current\ corner\ provided\n\ there\ is\ at\ least\ one\ there\ to\ pick.\ If\ there\ are\ no\ beepers\ on\ the\n\ corner,\ an\ error\ will\ be\ issued\ and\ the\ robot\ will\ turn\ off.\ If\ it\ is\ not\n\ running\ it\ does\ nothing.\n
comment14.params=
comment14.target=void\ putBeeper()
comment14.text=\n\ The\ robot\ will\ put\ exactly\ one\ beeper\ on\ the\ current\ corner\ provided\ that\n\ it\ has\ at\ least\ one\ in\ its\ beeper\ bag.\ If\ it\ has\ no\ beepers\ an\ error\ will\n\ be\ generated\ and\ the\ robot\ will\ turn\ off.\ If\ it\ is\ not\ running\ it\ does\n\ nothing.\n
comment15.params=
comment15.target=void\ turnOff()
comment15.text=\n\ The\ robot\ will\ turn\ off.\ After\ it\ turns\ off,\ it\ will\ no\ longer\ respond\ to\n\ the\ UrRobot\ commands.\n
