comment3.text=\n\ Create\ a\ robot\ facing\ a\ given\ direction\ EAST,\n\ NORTH,\ WEST,\ or\ SOUTH,\ with\ no\ beepers.\n\ \n\ @param\ direction\n\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ the\ direction\ the\ robot\ will\ initially\ face\n
comment4.params=direction\ beepers
comment4.target=UrRobot(Direction,\ int)
comment4.text=\n\ Create\ a\ robot\ facing\ a\ given\ direction\ with\ a\ given\ number\ of\ beepers\ in\n\ its\ beeper\ bag.\ If\ the\ number\ of\ beepers\ is\ negative\ it\ will\ be\n\ interpreted\ as\ infinitely\ many\ beepers.\ You\ may\ also\ use\ the\ constant\n\ KarelWorld.INFINITE\ for\ infinitely\ many\ beepers.\n\ \n\ @param\ direction\n\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ the\ direction\ the\ robot\ will\ initially\ face\n\ @param\ beepers\n\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ the\ initial\ number\ of\ beepers\ in\ the\ beeper\ bag\n
comment5.params=street\ avenue\ direction\ beepers
comment5.target=UrRobot(int,\ int,\ Direction,\ int)
